{"cursor":"7815","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nThe 'College of Pontiffs' (Latin 'Collegium Pontificum'; see [[collegium]]) was\na body of the ancient Roman state whose members were the highest-ranking priests\nof the state religion. The college consisted of the Pontifex Maximus and the\nother pontifices, the [[Rex Sacrorum]], the fifteen flamens, and the\nVestals. JÃ¶rg RÃ¼pke, \"Communicating with the Gods,\" in A Companion to Roman\nReligion, (Blackwell, 2010), p. 226; John A. North, \"The Constitution of the\nRoman Republic,\" in the same volume, p. 268 (a table showing priestly roles of\nRoman religion, including assignment to colleges). The College of Pontiffs\nwas one of the four major priestly colleges, the others being of the augurs, the\n[[quindecimviri sacris faciundis]] (\"fifteen men who carry out the rites\"), and\nthe Epulones.\n\nThe title [[pontiff|pontifex]] comes from the Latin for \"bridge builder\", a\npossible allusion to a very early role in placating the gods and spirits\nassociated with the Tiber River, for\ninstance. http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/ancient/7Cnuma.asp Also,\nVarro cites this position as meaning \"able to\ndo\". [http://books.google.com/books?id=xQd82l39KX4C&pg=PA195 Religions of\nRome, Vol. 2, pg 195]\n\nThe pontifex maximus was the most important member of the college. Until 104 BC,\nthe pontifex maximus held the sole power in appointing members to the other\npriesthoods in the college.\n\nThe flamens were priests in charge of fifteen official cults of Roman religion,\neach assigned to a particular god. The three major flamens ([[flamines\nmaiores]]) were the Flamen Dialis, the high priest of Jupiter; the Flamen\nMartialis, who cultivated Mars; and the Flamen Quirinalis, devoted to Quirinus.\nThe deities cultivated by the twelve [[flamines minores]] were Carmenta, Ceres,\nFalacer, Flora, Furrina, Palatua, Pomona, Portunes, Volcanus (Vulcan),\nVolturnus, and two whose names are lost.\n\nThe Vestal Virgins were the only female members of the college. They were in\ncharge of guarding Rome's sacred hearth, keeping the flame burning inside the\nTemple of Vesta. Around age 6 to 10, girls were chosen for this position and\nwere obligated to perform the rites and obligations, including remaining chaste,\nfor 30 years.\n","linknr":210,"url":"College_of_Pontiffs","recorded":1374543064,"links":["/w/index.php?title=College_of_Pontiffs&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=College_of_Pontiffs&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Pontifex_(disambiguation)","/wiki/File:Flamen_Louvre_Ma431.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7c/Flamen_Louvre_Ma431.jpg/169px-Flamen_Louvre_Ma431.jpg","/wiki/Flamen","/wiki/Collegium_(ancient_Rome)","/wiki/Augur","/wiki/Vestal_Virgin","/wiki/Flamen","/wiki/Epulones","/wiki/Quindecimviri_sacris_faciundis","/wiki/Glossary_of_ancient_Roman_religion#sodalitas","/wiki/Fetial","/wiki/Arval_Brethren","/wiki/Salii","/wiki/Titii","/wiki/Glossary_of_ancient_Roman_religion#Luperci","/wiki/Sodales_Augustales","/wiki/Pontifex_Maximus","/wiki/Rex_Sacrorum","/wiki/Flamen_Dialis","/wiki/Flamen_Martialis","/wiki/Flamen_Quirinalis","/wiki/Rex_Nemorensis","/wiki/Curio_maximus","/